Actress Tonto Dikeh has advised fans against emulating her as it concerns relationships. In an Instagram post, the 36-year-old media personality stated she had at some point in her life ignored the excesses of someone because of the love she had for the fellow. She described the act as one of the most toxic things she’s ever done. “One of the most toxic things I have ever done is ignore the bad in someone because I love them,” she wrote. The mother of one urged fans never to toe the same path. - Advertisement - “Don’t be me,” she added. Reacting to her post some social media users confessed to being guilty of same while many others affirmed ignoring people’s excesses only gives them the license to further misbehave.   Kenneth Okonkwo commends lady for accepting proposal on knee      Giving everyone access unhealthy – Mercy Johnson     Talent is never enough, says Uche Jombo   syvanking said: “Exactly because when you do that, you’ve given them the licence to misbehave.” _maame_tee16 wrote: “to be honest you’re the best King everrr. Exactly how I feel sometimes.” apinkeoflagos stated: “When you ignore for too long, they tend not to know their bad attitudes.” realqueenbrown said: “I swear but that would never happen to me again. Never!” princess_oma009 wrote: “And it’s hurting aswear, wen u overlook the bad things a person does to you all in the name of..u love them.” abikeade_wealth stated: “The story of my life.” luxeju_skinfuel said: “Absolutely.” Thekisocalvinia wrote: “That makes the two of us, but it was a lesson learned.” cruise_talker stated: “Tontolet it’s normal, we always overlook and make excuses for the people we love.”